reviews.review_text:
Great Recording Given the current release of recordings from the 1980 run at The Warfield I decided to give a listen to the full run, taking advantage of the Archive stash. This recording has its blemishes but it's a wonderful recording nonetheless. Clean, good fidelity, doesn't sound like in a tin can, good dynamic range... I don't like throwing 5-stars willy-nilly. Four-stars doesn't do it justice. So, while it's not perfect (perfection/beauty in the eye of the beholder) I'm giving it 5-stars.

Thanks to Mark for recording it. Thanks to Charlie and Scott for transfer and master. Given it's mastered Jan. 2019 this recording has not been available for very long. Glad I stumbled upon it. Long live the Grateful Dead. Dead 'til I die.

Good Times In 1995, after Jerry passed, I saw that PBS was airing the "Reckoning" video. But alas, I had no cable and this was before OnDemand was a thing. I called my mom and asked if she would please set her VCR (it was on at midnight, well after Mom's bedtime) and record it for me. She said she would, and I could get it from her when I came to visit, Now, Mom was under the impression that I was listening to death metal, (I do like the heavy stuff once in a while) and she had a picture of The Dead in her mind that was totally wrong. She told me later that she did indeed stay up that night so she could see what her son was poisoning his mind with. She said that she was not only surprised, but actually kind of enjoyed the songs. I was so proud of her! Then she lectured me about Metallica, Danzig, and Black Sabbath. Oh well...
Bonzo's Montreux I know nobody ever mentions it but this is the day John Bonham from Led Zeppelin passed .
